    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regional Deployment Controls for Claude Workloads"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data residency requirements specify where data may be processed and stored — typically expressed as 'must remain in the EU', 'must not leave the United States', or 'may only be processed in an approved jurisdiction list'. These requirements come from regulation (GDPR Article 44–49 for EU-to-third-country transfers), contract obligations (enterprise customers may contractually require data stays in a specific region), or internal policy (security teams may restrict processing to regions where the organization has infrastructure control)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Regional routing architecture — policy router directs Claude workloads to region-specific endpoints based on user region tag",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The routing architecture above shows the core pattern: every Claude API request carries a region identifier, and a policy router validates that the request is directed to an endpoint in an approved region before forwarding it. Requests from regions not approved for the data's classification tier are blocked."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic's Regional Endpoint Availability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic makes the Claude API available in multiple AWS regions. The specific regions available under your enterprise agreement depend on your contract. As of 2025, enterprise agreements can typically include access to US (us-east-1), EU (eu-west-1 / eu-central-1), and selected APAC regions. Confirm current region availability with your Anthropic account team — the available regions evolve as infrastructure expands."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Region-Specific API Endpoints"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, os\n\n# Region-specific base URLs — confirm actual URLs with your Anthropic account team\nREGIONAL_ENDPOINTS = {\n    \"us\":   \"https://api.anthropic.com\",                 # US (default)\n    \"eu\":   \"https://api.eu.anthropic.com\",              # EU (hypothetical; confirm with Anthropic)\n    \"apac\": \"https://api.apac.anthropic.com\",            # APAC (hypothetical; confirm with Anthropic)\n}\n\ndef get_regional_client(region: str) -> anthropic.Anthropic:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return an Anthropic client pointed at the correct regional endpoint.\n    The API key may be region-specific if your contract scopes keys by region.\n    \"\"\"\n    base_url = REGIONAL_ENDPOINTS.get(region.lower())\n    if not base_url:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Region '{region}' not in approved endpoint list\")\n\n    # Region-specific key stored separately in secrets manager\n    api_key = os.environ.get(f\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_{region.upper()}\")\n    if not api_key:\n        raise EnvironmentError(f\"No API key configured for region {region}\")\n\n    return anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=api_key, base_url=base_url)\n\n# Usage\neu_client = get_regional_client(\"eu\")\nresp = eu_client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Summarize this EU contract clause...\"}],\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Never use the default US endpoint for EU-resident personal data if your DPA requires EU data residency. A misdirected request constitutes a cross-border transfer — the technical architecture must enforce residency, not just policy documents."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing a Regional Policy Router"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The policy router is the component that maps each request to the correct regional endpoint and blocks requests from unauthorized regions. It sits between your application and the Anthropic API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Router Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nimport anthropic, os\n\n@dataclass\nclass RegionalPolicy:\n    allowed_regions: list[str]\n    default_region: str\n    block_unknown_regions: bool = True\n\n# Policy per data classification — more restrictive classifications get tighter region lists\nCLASSIFICATION_POLICIES = {\n    \"PUBLIC\":       RegionalPolicy([\"us\", \"eu\", \"apac\"], default_region=\"us\", block_unknown_regions=False),\n    \"INTERNAL\":     RegionalPolicy([\"us\", \"eu\", \"apac\"], default_region=\"us\"),\n    \"CONFIDENTIAL\": RegionalPolicy([\"us\", \"eu\"],          default_region=\"us\"),\n    \"RESTRICTED\":   RegionalPolicy([\"us\"],                default_region=\"us\"),  # US only by default\n}\n\nREGIONAL_ENDPOINTS = {\n    \"us\":   \"https://api.anthropic.com\",\n    \"eu\":   \"https://api.eu.anthropic.com\",   # confirm with Anthropic\n    \"apac\": \"https://api.apac.anthropic.com\", # confirm with Anthropic\n}\n\nclass RegionalRouter:\n    def route(\n        self,\n        user_region: str,\n        data_classification: str,\n        model: str,\n        messages: list,\n        **kwargs,\n    ):\n        policy = CLASSIFICATION_POLICIES.get(data_classification)\n        if not policy:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown classification: {data_classification}\")\n\n        region = user_region.lower()\n        if region not in policy.allowed_regions:\n            if policy.block_unknown_regions:\n                raise PermissionError(\n                    f\"Region '{region}' not approved for {data_classification} data. \"\n                    f\"Approved regions: {policy.allowed_regions}\"\n                )\n            region = policy.default_region  # fall back for PUBLIC\n\n        base_url = REGIONAL_ENDPOINTS[region]\n        api_key = os.environ[f\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_{region.upper()}\"]\n        client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=api_key, base_url=base_url)\n\n        return client.messages.create(model=model, messages=messages, **kwargs), region"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting User Region"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Determine user region from request context\n# Priority: explicit override > authenticated user profile > IP geolocation\n\ndef detect_user_region(request_headers: dict, user_profile: dict | None) -> str:\n    # 1. Explicit header (set by frontend or gateway)\n    if \"X-User-Region\" in request_headers:\n        return request_headers[\"X-User-Region\"].lower()\n\n    # 2. Authenticated user's registered region (from HR/identity system)\n    if user_profile and user_profile.get(\"data_residency_region\"):\n        return user_profile[\"data_residency_region\"].lower()\n\n    # 3. IP geolocation (least reliable — use only as fallback)\n    cf_country = request_headers.get(\"CF-IPCountry\", \"\")  # Cloudflare header\n    EU_COUNTRIES = {\"DE\", \"FR\", \"NL\", \"BE\", \"IT\", \"ES\", \"PL\", \"SE\", \"AT\", \"CH\"}\n    APAC_COUNTRIES = {\"JP\", \"AU\", \"SG\", \"KR\", \"IN\", \"TW\"}\n    if cf_country in EU_COUNTRIES:\n        return \"eu\"\n    if cf_country in APAC_COUNTRIES:\n        return \"apac\"\n    return \"us\"  # default"
          }
        ]
      },
