      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The EU endpoint is the most straightforward mechanism for EU data residency compliance — when data never leaves the EU, Chapter V GDPR transfer restrictions do not apply. However, if your enterprise agreement does not explicitly guarantee that the EU endpoint processes data exclusively within the EU, you still need SCCs as a fallback."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Region-Specific API Key Management"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regional routing requires region-specific API key management. Using a single global API key for all regions creates several problems: you cannot isolate a regional incident, you cannot set region-specific rate limits or spending controls, and you lose the audit granularity to prove that EU requests were handled only by the EU endpoint."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Recommended API key structure for multi-region deployments:\n\nProduction keys (one per region per classification tier):\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_US_INTERNAL       → us-east-1, INTERNAL and below\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_US_CONFIDENTIAL   → us-east-1, CONFIDENTIAL and below\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_EU_INTERNAL       → eu-west-1, INTERNAL and below\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_EU_CONFIDENTIAL   → eu-west-1, CONFIDENTIAL and below\n\nRESTRICTED keys (if applicable):\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_US_RESTRICTED     → us-east-1, dedicated RESTRICTED workloads only\n  ANTHROPIC_KEY_EU_RESTRICTED     → eu-west-1, dedicated RESTRICTED workloads only\n\nRotation schedule: 90 days for INTERNAL; 30 days for CONFIDENTIAL and above\nStorage: secrets manager (Vault / AWS Secrets Manager / Azure Key Vault)\nNever store in: environment variables in shared CI/CD, version control, application logs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Rotation Automation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import boto3, datetime\n\ndef rotate_regional_key(\n    secret_name: str,\n    region_name: str,\n    anthropic_admin_token: str,\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    Rotate an Anthropic API key stored in AWS Secrets Manager.\n    1. Create a new key via Anthropic admin API\n    2. Store the new key in Secrets Manager\n    3. Verify new key works\n    4. Revoke the old key\n    \"\"\"\n    import requests, anthropic\n\n    # Step 1: Create new key via Anthropic admin API (requires admin token)\n    resp = requests.post(\n        \"https://api.anthropic.com/v1/organizations/api-keys\",\n        headers={\"anthropic-beta\": \"account-management-2024-10-30\",\n                 \"x-api-key\": anthropic_admin_token},\n        json={\"name\": f\"{secret_name}-{datetime.date.today().isoformat()}\"},\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    new_key = resp.json()[\"key\"][\"secret\"]\n    new_key_id = resp.json()[\"key\"][\"id\"]\n\n    # Step 2: Store in Secrets Manager\n    sm = boto3.client(\"secretsmanager\", region_name=region_name)\n    old_secret = sm.get_secret_value(SecretId=secret_name)[\"SecretString\"]\n    sm.put_secret_value(SecretId=secret_name, SecretString=new_key)\n\n    # Step 3: Verify new key\n    test_client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=new_key)\n    test_client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", max_tokens=5,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"ping\"}]\n    )\n\n    # Step 4: Revoke old key (parse ID from stored value if needed)\n    # requests.delete(f\"https://api.anthropic.com/v1/organizations/api-keys/{old_key_id}\", ...)\n\n    return new_key_id"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monitoring and Alerting for Region Violations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Technical controls prevent most region violations, but monitoring catches the cases that slip through: misconfigured routing, hardcoded endpoints in legacy code, or cross-region fallback behavior that was not intended to apply to sensitive data."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Region Violation Alerts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"region-compliance\")\n\ndef log_and_alert_region_routing(\n    user_region: str,\n    data_classification: str,\n    routed_to: str,\n    policy_approved_regions: list[str],\n    request_id: str,\n):\n    entry = {\n        \"request_id\": request_id,\n        \"user_region\": user_region,\n        \"data_classification\": data_classification,\n        \"routed_to\": routed_to,\n        \"violation\": routed_to not in policy_approved_regions,\n    }\n    if entry[\"violation\"]:\n        logger.error(f\"REGION_VIOLATION: {entry}\")\n        # Send to SIEM / alerting system — page on-call for CONFIDENTIAL+\n        alert_security_team(entry)\n    else:\n        logger.info(f\"region_routing: {entry}\")\n\ndef alert_security_team(event: dict):\n    # Implementation: send to PagerDuty, Slack, or SIEM webhook\n    pass"
          }
        ]
      },
