        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Regional Controls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regional routing controls must be tested in staging before production deployment, and periodically re-tested after infrastructure changes. The test suite verifies that the router correctly enforces approved-region lists and blocks unauthorized routing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import pytest\n\nrouter = RegionalRouter()\n\nclass TestRegionalRouter:\n    def test_eu_internal_routes_to_eu(self):\n        _, region = router.route(\"eu\", \"INTERNAL\", \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                                  [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"test\"}], max_tokens=5)\n        assert region == \"eu\"\n\n    def test_eu_restricted_blocked(self):\n        \"\"\"RESTRICTED data only approved for US by default policy.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(PermissionError):\n            router.route(\"eu\", \"RESTRICTED\", \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                          [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"test\"}], max_tokens=5)\n\n    def test_unknown_region_public_falls_back(self):\n        \"\"\"Unknown regions fall back to default for PUBLIC data (block_unknown=False).\"\"\"\n        _, region = router.route(\"xx\", \"PUBLIC\", \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                                  [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"test\"}], max_tokens=5)\n        assert region == \"us\"  # default for PUBLIC\n\n    def test_unknown_region_internal_blocked(self):\n        \"\"\"Unknown regions are blocked for INTERNAL and above.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(PermissionError):\n            router.route(\"xx\", \"INTERNAL\", \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                          [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"test\"}], max_tokens=5)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regional deployment controls for Claude workloads require three things working in concert: a regional policy router that maps data classifications to approved endpoint regions; region-specific API keys stored in a secrets manager with automated rotation; and monitoring that alerts on any request reaching a non-approved region. For EU-resident personal data, the EU endpoint eliminates the cross-border transfer question entirely — data that never leaves the EU does not trigger GDPR Chapter V requirements. Build the routing logic into the infrastructure layer (API gateway or service mesh), not the application layer, so it cannot be bypassed by individual teams. Verify regional controls with an automated test suite that runs on every deployment."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
